        <body>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <head type="title">MS III Second Poetry Anthology</head>
                <!--An apparatus may contain all or only some of the following sections.-->
                <div type="section" xml:id="WITNESSES">
                    <head type="section">Witnesses</head>
                    <list type="simple">
                        <item><ref type="witness" target="constellations_msiii.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHECONSTELLATIONS">&#x201C;The Constellations: Northern, Some of the Zodiac, and
                            Some of the Southern&#x201D;;</title></ref></item>
                        <item><ref type="witness" target="time_blank_verse_msiii.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTIMEBLANKVERSE">&#x201C;Time: Blank Verse&#x201D;;</title></ref></item>
                        <item><ref type="witness" target="the_sun_msiii.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHESUN">&#x201C;The Sun&#x201D;;</title></ref></item>
                        <item><ref type="witness" target="glen_of_glenfarg_msiii.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRGLENFARG">&#x201C;Glen of Glenfarg&#x201D; (&#x201C;Papa how
                            pretty those icicles are&#x201D;);</title></ref></item>
                        <item><ref type="witness" target="look_at_that_ship_msiii.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHESHIP1827">&#x201C;The Ship&#x201D; [<date when="1827">1827</date>];</title></ref></item>
                        <item><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHEBRITISHBATTLES">&#x201C;The British Battles.&#x201D;</title></item>
                    </list>
                </div>
                <div type="section" xml:id="TITLE">
                    <head type="section">Title</head>
                    <p><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> entitled the collection &#x201C;<hi rend="caps"
                        >Poetry</hi>,&#x201D; just as he had headed the <title type="anthology" corresp="#MSIPOETRYANTHOLOGY">MS I Poetry Anthology</title>
                        as &#x201C;Poetry&#x201D;.</p>
                </div>
                <!--<div type="section" xml:id="GENRE">
                    <head type="section">Genre</head>
                    <p>Body paragraph.</p>
                </div>-->
                <div type="section" xml:id="MAJORMS">
                    <head type="section">Manuscripts</head>
                    <p>Body paragraph.</p>
                </div>
                    <div type="section" xml:id="CONTENTS">
                        <head type="section">Contents</head>
                        <p>The anthology contains the following poems, in order of their appearance:</p>
                        <list type="ordered">
                            <item><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHECONSTELLATIONS">&#x201C;The Constellations: Northern, Some of the Zodiac, and
                                Some of the Southern&#x201D;;</title></item>
                            <item><ref type="apparatus" target="time_blank_verse_apparatus.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTIMEBLANKVERSE">&#x201C;Time: Blank Verse&#x201D;;</title></ref></item>
                            <item><ref type="apparatus" target="the_sun_apparatus.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHESUN">&#x201C;The Sun&#x201D;;</title></ref></item>
                            <item><ref type="apparatus" target="glenfarg_apparatus.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRGLENFARG">&#x201C;Glen of Glenfarg&#x201D; (&#x201C;Papa how
                                pretty those icicles are&#x201D;);</title></ref></item>
                            <item><ref type="apparatus" target="look_at_that_ship_apparatus.php"><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHESHIP1827">&#x201C;The Ship&#x201D; [<date when="1827">1827</date>];</title></ref></item>
                            <item><title type="poem" corresp="#JRTHEBRITISHBATTLES">&#x201C;The British Battles.&#x201D;</title></item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                <div type="section" xml:id="DATE">
                    <head type="section">Date</head>
                    <p><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> compiled this anthology in <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title> in <date when="1828">1828</date>, sometime after <date when="1828-01-01">New
                        Year&#x02BC;s Day</date>, making it the second anthology in this <title type="manuscript" corresp="#JRREDBOOK">Red Book</title>, after
                        <title type="anthology" corresp="#POETRYDESCRIPTIVE">Poetry Descriptive</title> (<date when="1827">1827</date>) (see <ref type="apparatus" target="msiii_apparatus.php#DISCUSSION"><title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>: Discussion</ref>; see also <ref type="apparatus" subtype="manuscript" target="msiii_poetry_anthology_3_apparatus.php">MS III Third Poetry
                        Anthology</ref>).</p>
                </div>
                <div type="section" xml:id="COMPILATION">
                    <head type="section">Compilation</head>
                    <p>A drawing, <title type="artwork" corresp="#JRSHIPANDHOUSEMSIII">Ship and House</title>, [Miscellaneous Drawing, <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>], falls within the
                        anthology, and probably predates it. <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> probably intended the drawing to
                        illustrate <title type="lesson" corresp="#JRHARRYANDLUCYVOL2">&#x201C;Harry and Lucy,&#x201D; Vol. 2</title>, but, ending the
                        narrative earlier than expected, wrapped the drawing round by <title type="poem" corresp="#JRTIMEBLANKVERSE">&#x201C;Time:
                        Blank Verse.&#x201D;</title> Another drawing, <title type="artwork" corresp="#JRRAGLANDCASTLEMSIII">&#x201C;Ragland Castle When
                        Newly Built,&#x201D;</title> [Miscellaneous Drawing, <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>], forms the terminus of
                        the anthology and, again, probably predates it, but this drawing can be dated
                        less securely (see <ref type="apparatus" target="msiii_apparatus#DISCUSSION">MS III: Discussion</ref>; <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="msiii_drawings_note.php">MS III Drawings</ref>).</p>
                </div>
                <div type="section" xml:id="THEMES">
                    <head type="section">Themes</head>
                    <p>See <ref type="apparatus" target="poetry_descriptive_apparatus.php"><title type="anthology" corresp="#POETRYDESCRIPTIVE">Poetry Descriptive</title></ref> for <persName corresp="#WGC">W. G. Collingwood</persName>&#x02BC;s assumption that this
                        collection along with the second form a single anthology. Of the second
                        anthology, however, only <title type="poem" corresp="#JRGLENFARG">&#x201C;Glen of Glenfarg&#x201D;
                        (&#x201C;Papa how pretty those icicles are&#x201D;)</title> is
                        &#x201C;descriptive&#x201D; in the topographical sense of the earlier
                        collection, the second being dominated more by catalog poetry and New
                        Year&#x02BC;s poetry.</p>
                    <p>Body paragraph containing a list:
                        <list type="ordered">
                            <item n="1">First item in the list.</item>
                            <item n="2">Second item.</item>
                            <item n="3">Third item.</item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
                    <p>Body paragraph.</p>
                </div>
                
            </div>
